# Task tracking

## Active tasklist (every session)

- Maintain an active tasklist throughout the session using the tool's task mechanism.
- Seed it at session start with known open items before beginning work.
- Create tasks proactively as new work surfaces — yak-shaving and deferred items too,
  not just the primary request.
- Mark tasks completed promptly; never let the list go stale.

## todo.txt / done.txt

- If `todo.txt`/`done.txt` don't exist at the repo root, create them
  (`touch todo.txt done.txt`).
- Use `todo.sh` for all todo.txt/done.txt operations; fall back to direct file edits
  only when the CLI isn't installed.
- Priorities: `(A)` blocking · `(B)` important · `(C)` maintenance · none = nice-to-have.
- Completing a deferred item → move it to done.txt with an `x YYYY-MM-DD` prefix
  (`todo.sh archive` convention); never delete completed tasks.
- Keep the session tasklist and todo.txt in sync.

## Pane label (tmux)

When running under tmux, once the task is identifiable set the pane title to a short task
summary: `tmux select-pane -T "<label>"`, guarded by `[[ -n "${TMUX:-}" ]] &&`. Sync it to
the todo.txt task slug; refine as understanding improves.
{{- if hasPrefix "dot_claude/" $.chezmoi.sourceFile }}
Persist the label to `~/.claude/task-labels/$TMUX_PANE` (read by the `UserPromptSubmit`
hook) so agent refinements override the auto-label and persist across user messages.
{{- end }}
